1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method for completing multidimensional arrays using a tensor-Singular Value Decomposition (t-SVD) and a convex optimization problem. This falls under the domain of machine learning and hence cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions the application of the proposed method to panning video sequences, which is a common problem in computer vision. Hence, cs.CV is a likely sub-category.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the notion of tensor rank and its optimality properties, which is related to information theory. Hence, cs.IT is a likely sub-category.
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a convex optimization problem for completing multidimensional arrays, which involves numerical methods. Hence, cs.NA is a likely sub-category.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the problem of completing multidimensional arrays from limited sampling, which involves designing efficient algorithms. Hence, cs.DS is a likely sub-category.
